title.narrative: 2.1. By 2021, social and child protection practitioners have increased capacity to assist families in situations of particular vulnerability/at risk of separation to provide care for their children, preventing institutionalization.

description.narrative: Gaining a momentum around children's de-institutionalisation (DI) from residential care, UNICEF spearheaded coalition triggered a significant system response to children's right of living in a family environment. As a result, 240 children residing in public institutions started benefitting from the support tailored to their specific needs; the Government committed to transform all public residential institutions into family strengthening hubs and UNICEF was asked to technically support the implementation of the DI national action plan. Moreover, UNICEF commissioned in-service training curricula for child protection practitioners, imbedded in the Albanian School of Public Administration. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:09/01/2020
